	  upper bits, (ie. (char)0xff00 -> 0) so it's better to test if
	  nonzero and set 0 or 1 instead of simply casting ... as a flag usage.
	  (but I believe this won't cause actual bug in current implementation)
	  [ruby-dev:27055]

